The proof of `infinity_of_primes₄` relies on the inequality `log x ≤ π(x) + 1`. This can be derived by bounding the Euler product $\prod_{p \le x} \frac{p}{p-1}$. We use the fact that the $k$-th prime $p_k \ge k+2$ (since $p_0=2, p_1=3, \dots$), which implies $\frac{p_k}{p_k-1} \le \frac{k+2}{k+1}$. The product of these terms telescopes to $\pi(x) + 1$.

